{#- Changelog ‚Äî tabular rendering.

    One row per version; most recent first. Inline delta cells use the
    `+A / ~C / -R` shorthand (added / changed / resolved). A detail block
    immediately below the table enumerates T-IDs for the latest entry
    (capped at `_max`) so the most recent run is easy to audit without
    scrolling the table horizontally.

    Data shape per entry (see schemas/threat-model.output.schema.yaml):
      version, date, mode, baseline_sha, current_sha
      changed_files, changed_lines ({insertions, deletions})
      added:    { threats: [T-NNN,...], components: [C-NN,...], attack_surface: [E-NN,...] }
      changed:  { threats: [T-NNN,...], notes_by_id: { T-NNN: "..." } }
      resolved: { threats: [T-NNN,...], reason_by_id: { T-NNN: "..." } }
      reanalyzed_components, carried_forward_components, note
-#}
{%- set _max = 10 -%}
## Changelog

_Append-only history of assessment runs. Most recent first._

| Version | Date | Mode | Depth | Reasoning | Baseline ‚Üí Current | Œî Threats | Code | Note |
|---------|------|------|-------|-----------|--------------------|-----------|------|------|
{% for entry in changelog %}
{%- set v             = entry.version -%}
{%- set date          = entry.date or '‚Äî' -%}
{%- set mode          = (entry.mode or 'full') | lower -%}
{%- set depth         = (entry.assessment_depth or '‚Äî') | lower -%}
{%- set reasoning     = entry.reasoning_model or '‚Äî' -%}
{%- set baseline_sha  = entry.baseline_sha or '' -%}
{%- set current_sha   = entry.current_sha or '' -%}
{%- set has_baseline  = (baseline_sha | length) > 0 -%}
{%- set short_base    = baseline_sha[:7] -%}
{%- set short_cur     = current_sha[:7] if current_sha else '‚Äî' -%}
{%- set added_t       = (entry.added.threats   if entry.added   else []) | default([]) -%}
{%- set changed_t     = (entry.changed.threats if entry.changed else []) | default([]) -%}
{%- set resolved_t    = (entry.resolved.threats if entry.resolved else []) | default([]) -%}
{%- set changed_files = entry.changed_files -%}
{%- set cl            = entry.changed_lines or {} -%}
{%- set ins           = cl.insertions -%}
{%- set dels          = cl.deletions -%}
{%- set note          = (entry.note or '') | trim -%}
{#- Aggressive truncation ‚Äî the table row is narrow; long notes wrap the
    whole changelog illegibly. Upstream the orchestrator is instructed to
    keep `note` ‚â§12 words. -#}
{%- if note|length > 60 -%}{%- set note = note[:58] ~ '‚Ä¶' -%}{%- endif -%}
{%- if note -%}{%- set note = note | replace('|', '\\|') -%}{%- endif -%}
{%- set delta_cell = '+' ~ (added_t|length) ~ ' / ~' ~ (changed_t|length) ~ ' / -' ~ (resolved_t|length) -%}
{%- if has_baseline -%}
{%- set sha_cell = '`' ~ short_base ~ '` ‚Üí `' ~ short_cur ~ '`' -%}
{%- elif v == 1 and mode == 'full' -%}
{%- set sha_cell = '_(initial)_' -%}
{%- else -%}
{%- set sha_cell = '‚Äî' -%}
{%- endif -%}
{%- set code_parts = [] -%}
{%- if changed_files is not none and changed_files -%}
{%- set _ = code_parts.append((changed_files|string) ~ ' files') -%}
{%- endif -%}
{%- if ins is not none and dels is not none -%}
{%- set _ = code_parts.append('+' ~ ins ~ '/-' ~ dels) -%}
{%- endif -%}
{%- set code_cell = code_parts | join(', ') if code_parts else '‚Äî' -%}
| v{{ v }} | {{ date }} | {{ mode }} | {{ depth }} | {{ reasoning }} | {{ sha_cell }} | {{ delta_cell }} | {{ code_cell }} | {{ note or '‚Äî' }} |
{%- endfor %}
